[background arg="res://Bg/computer_lab.png" fade="1.0"]
audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/chill.mp3" [loop="true"]
set {c2s2_santos_tried} = false
set {c2s2_outsider_tried} = false
set {c2s2_alex_tried} = false
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/The_computer_lab_hums.mp3" volume="0.0"]
The computer lab hums with the sound of cooling fans. Ryan sits alone at a terminal, typing rapidly.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Ryan (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_looks_up_his_expression.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan looks up, his expression immediately guarded.
	Ryan: Great. More people coming to interrogate me.
	Celestine: We're not interrogating anyone. Just gathering information.
	Ryan: That's what everyone says before they point fingers.
	Celestine: We're trying to find the truth, Ryan. Not assign blame.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_crosses_his_arms.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan crosses his arms, but his posture relaxes slightly.
	Ryan: Fine. What do you want to know?
	Celestine: You were here yesterday evening. What were you working on?
	Ryan: My budget proposal. The one the council rejected last week.
	Celestine: Why were you revising a rejected proposal?
	Ryan: Because they were wrong to reject it. I was adding more data to prove my point.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_s_voice_with_frustration.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan's voice rises with frustration.
	Ryan: Do you know how much the council wastes on decorations? Fifteen thousand pesos for Foundation Day banners.
	Ryan: Meanwhile, the basketball team is using balls held together with tape.
	Celestine: That sounds frustrating.
	Ryan: Frustrating doesn't begin to cover it. I've been fighting for better resource allocation for months.
	Ryan: Nobody listens. They just smile and vote no.
	Celestine: Where were you between 6\:30 and 7\:00 yesterday?
	Ryan: Here. Printing documents. The printer kept jamming.
	Celestine: Did you leave the lab at any point during that time?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_hesitates_for_just_a_moment.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan hesitates for just a moment.
	Ryan: I... went to the bathroom once. Maybe 6\:40? It was just a few minutes.
	Celestine: Did you see anyone in the hallway?
	Ryan: Ms. Santos was walking toward the cafeteria. Probably getting coffee.
	Ryan: And I think I saw Alex heading toward the faculty room around the same time.
	Celestine: Alex? The former treasurer?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_shrugs.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan shrugs.
	Ryan: Yeah. She was carrying some folders. Probably club stuff.
	Celestine: Anyone else?
	Ryan: No. The building was pretty empty by then.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_stands_abruptly.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan stands abruptly.
	Ryan: Look, I didn't take the money. I have my complaints about the council, but I'm not a thief.
	Ryan: Now if you'll excuse me, I have work to do.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_returns_to_his_computer.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan returns to his computer, typing more aggressively than before.
	leave Ryan
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: He seemed pretty defensive. And that hesitation about leaving the lab...
	Celestine: He admitted to being in the hallway around the same time Ms. Santos was away.
	Celestine: And he mentioned seeing Alex near the faculty room. Interesting.
	Celestine: Let's talk to Ms. Santos next.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Ryan (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ryan_looks_up_his_expression.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan looks up, his expression immediately guarded.
