[background arg="res://Bg/faculty_empty.png" fade="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/The_faculty_room_is_quiet.mp3" volume="0.0"]
The faculty room is quiet. Ms. Santos sits at her desk, surrounded by stacks of papers.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join "Ms Santos" (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ms._Santos_looks_up_with_tired_eyes.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ms. Santos looks up with tired eyes. Dark circles suggest she hasn't slept well.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/She_sighs_heavily.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	She sighs heavily.
	"Ms Santos": More questions. I've already spoken to the principal twice.
	Celestine: We're sorry to bother you, Ma'am. We just want to understand what happened.
	"Ms Santos": What's there to understand? I was careless, and now a student is being blamed for it.
	Celestine: Can you walk us through yesterday evening?
	"Ms Santos": I was grading papers. Test week means mountains of work.
	"Ms Santos": I stayed until 8 PM to finish the Grade 9 exams.
	Celestine: Did you leave your desk at any point?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ms._Santos_fidgets_with_a_pen.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ms. Santos fidgets with a pen, avoiding eye contact.
	"Ms Santos": I... took a coffee break around 6\:30. Maybe fifteen minutes.
	Celestine: Did you lock your desk drawer before leaving?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Her_voice_drops_to_barely.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Her voice drops to barely above a whisper.
	"Ms Santos": I'm not sure. I might have forgotten.
	"Ms Santos": With all the grading, I've been so scattered lately. Small things slip my mind.
	Celestine: The council office key is kept in that drawer, correct?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Her_tone_becomes_defensive.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Her tone becomes defensive.
	"Ms Santos": Yes. And I know what you're thinking.
	"Ms Santos": I'm the one who let this happen. If I had just remembered to lock it...
	Celestine: We're not blaming you, Ma'am. We're trying to understand who had opportunity.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Ms._Santos_slumps_in_her_hair.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	"Ms Santos" slumps in her chair.
	"Ms Santos": Anyone could have taken that key during my break. The faculty room door was unlocked.
	Celestine: Did you see anyone when you returned from your break?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/She_pauses_to_think.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	She pauses to think.
	"Ms Santos": When I was coming back... I think I saw Ryan. Near the stairwell.
	"Ms Santos": And now that I think about it... Alex was in the hallway too.
	Celestine: Alex? The former treasurer?
	"Ms Santos": Yes. She said she was returning some club documents. Asked if she could leave them on my desk.
	"Ms Santos": I told her to just put them in the inbox by the door.
	Celestine: What time was that?
	"Ms Santos": Around 6\:45. Maybe a few minutes before.
	Celestine: Did Alex go into the faculty room?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Uncertainty_crosses_her_face.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Uncertainty crosses her face.
	"Ms Santos": I... I don't know. I went to get my coffee. She was still in the hallway when I left.
	Celestine: Thank you, Ma'am. This is helpful.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/c2s2 narrator mathilda/Ms santos leaves.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	leave "Ms Santos"
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: So both Ryan and Alex were near the faculty room during Ms. Santos's break.
	Celestine: And Alex had a reason to be there. "Returning documents."
	Mark: A perfect excuse to slip in and grab the key.
	Celestine: We need to talk to Alex.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join "Ms Santos" (half) right
