[background arg="res://Bg/hallway.png" fade="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/They_find_Alex_near_the_bulletin_board.mp3" volume="0.0"]
They find Alex near the bulletin board, studying the club announcements.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Alex (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_turns_as_they_approach.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex turns as they approach, her expression wary.
	Alex: Let me guess. You're here about the missing money.
	Celestine: Word travels fast.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Bitterness_creeps_in_her_voice.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Bitterness creeps into her voice.
	Alex: Especially when people are looking for someone to blame besides precious Ria.
	Celestine: You sound frustrated.
	Alex: Wouldn't you be? I was treasurer for two years. Never lost a single peso.
	Alex: Then Ria comes in with her "fresh ideas" and suddenly I'm yesterday's news.
	Celestine: You were here yesterday evening. What were you doing?
	Alex: Club committee meeting. We finished around 6\:30.
	Celestine: And after that?
	Alex: I had some old documents to return to the faculty room.
	Alex: Club budget records from last year. They needed them for the audit.
	Celestine: Did you go inside the faculty room?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_hesistates_crossing.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex hesitates, crossing her arms defensively.
	Alex: I... stepped in briefly. Ms. Santos wasn't there.
	Alex: I left the folders in her inbox and left. That's it.
	Celestine: Did you see anyone else?
	Alex: Ryan was lurking around. Near the stairs.
	Alex: He's always complaining about the budget. Wouldn't surprise me if he finally snapped.
	Celestine: You seem to know a lot about what happened.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_s_tone_turns_defensive.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex's tone turns defensive.
	Alex: Because I was there! And because I actually pay attention.
	Alex: Unlike some people who just waltz in and take over positions they didn't earn.
	Mark: You mean Ria?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_scoffs.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex scoffs.
	Alex: She made mistakes I never would have made. Leaving the lockbox unlocked overnight?
	Alex: If I were still treasurer, this never would have happened.
	Celestine: How do you know about Ria's mistake last year?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_s _expression_flickers.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex's expression flickers for just a moment.
	Alex: Everyone knows. Council gossip travels fast.
	Alex: Look, I didn't take the money. I have nothing to prove and nothing to gain.
	Alex: If you want a suspect, look at the guy who's been publicly ranting about budget waste for months.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S2/Alex_waks_away.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Alex walks away before The Protagonist can ask more questions.
	leave Alex
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: She's bitter about being replaced. And she knew about Ria's mistake.
	Celestine: She also admitted to being in the faculty room when Ms. Santos was gone.
	Mark: Just like Ryan was in the hallway at the same time.
	Celestine: Two people with motive. Two people with opportunity.
	Celestine: The timeline is getting complicated.
	Mark: So who do we focus on?
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Alex (half) right
